    <text type="letter">
        <body>           
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01612.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Washington D. C.</name>
                    <date when="1876-05-02">May 2. 1876</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Enclosed I send you a copy of a letter received by William.<ptr target="loc.00575_n100"/> 
                He says he knew the writer by correspondence only, when he was on the Saturday <choice><abbr>Eve'g</abbr><expan>Evening</expan></choice> 
                Post. Her name was then Fanny Malone Raymond,<ptr target="loc.02893_n4"/> and she was said to be extremely 
                beautiful and probably is so yet.</p>   
            <p>You had better accept their invitation&#8212;How did you
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01612.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                like <choice><sic>Williams</sic><corr>William's</corr></choice> article?<ptr target="loc.01612_n"/> And how is your health. 
                write me if you can&#8212;All your friends well here as far as I know.</p>           
            <closer>
                <salute>Faithfully Yours</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">Charley.</hi></signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
